1,496 chars on a clean build — well within the 4,000 target and far from the 6,000 cap. Expands naturally when tests fail or clippy fires.

**What `.lathe/snapshot.sh` collects:**

| Section | Happy path | Failure path |
|---|---|---|
| Git status | `--short` output | — |
| Recent commits | 10 onelines | — |
| Build | "OK — builds clean" | First 10 `error:` lines |
| Tests | Pass/Fail/Ignored counts | First 15 failure lines |
| Clippy | "OK — no warnings" | Error count + first 10 |
| Audit | "OK — no unsafe/leak/net" | Exact violations |
| CI | Workflow filenames | "No CI config" |
| FLS Fixtures | Fixture file count | — |

Key details:
- `gtimeout`/`timeout` fallback for macOS
- `|| true` on all commands that might fail (tests, clippy, grep)
- `2>&1` captures stderr from cargo
- Audit section runs statically (grep) — no compilation needed, zero cost
